olive oil
2 clove garlic
1 unit Baby Leaves
1 packet button mushrooms
1 packet Beef Mince
1 sachet Tex-Mex spice blend
1 packet tomato paste
1 tsp brown sugar
⅓ cup water
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese
1 packet sour cream

• Preheat oven to 200°C/180°C fan-forced.
• Finely chop garlic. Roughly chop baby leaves. Thinly slice mushrooms.
• Heat a large frying pan over high heat.

• Return the frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Add mushrooms and cook until browned and softened, 5 minutes.
• Increase the heat to high and cook beef mince, breaking up with a spoon, until browned, 3-4 minutes.

• SPICY! This is a mild spice blend, but use less if you're sensitive to heat! Add garlic and Tex-Mex spice blend to the pan and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add tomato paste, the brown sugar and water and cook, stirring, until slightly thickened, 1-2 minutes. Season to taste.

• Arrange mini flour tortillas on a lined oven tray. Divide beef filling between tortillas, spooning it onto one half of each tortilla, then top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
• Fold the empty half of each tortilla over to enclose the filling and press down gently with a spatula. Brush (or spray) the tortillas with a drizzle of olive oil, then season with salt and pepper.
• Bake quesadillas until cheese has melted and tortillas are golden, 10-12 minutes. Spoon any overflowing filling back into the quesadillas.

• While the quesadillas are baking, add baby leaves to a bowl, along with a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil.
Season, then stir to combine.

• Divide Tex-Mex beef quesadillas between plates.
• Serve with sour cream. Enjoy!

TIP: Cut the quesadillas into wedges if you prefer!